US Cranking War Back Up In Somalia
President Joe Biden is cranking back up the US government’s war in Somalia. Previously, President Donald Trump brought some reprieve in US military action in the African nation. But, intervention reducing developments in US foreign policy tend to face much pressure to end. In a Monday article at the New York Times, Charlie Savage and Eric Schmitt relate some of the new developments in US military action in Somalia. The article begins with the following reporting of key developments:
President Biden has signed an order authorizing the military to once again deploy hundreds of Special Operations forces inside Somalia — largely reversing the decision by President Donald J. Trump to withdraw nearly all 700 ground troops who had been stationed there, according to four officials familiar with the matter.
In addition, Mr. Biden has approved a Pentagon request for standing authority to target about a dozen suspected leaders of Al Shabab, the Somali terrorist group that is affiliated with Al Qaeda, three of the officials said. Since Mr. Biden took office, airstrikes have largely been limited to those meant to defend partner forces facing an immediate threat.
Together, the decisions by Mr. Biden, described by the officials on the condition of anonymity, will revive an open-ended American counterterrorism operation that has amounted to a slow-burn war through three administrations. The move stands in contrast to his decision last year to pull American forces from Afghanistan, saying that “it is time to end the forever war.”

Judge Christopher “Casey” Cooper

God bless you as you continue to pray your rosary in this month of May.

Every chance they get, the Democrat Party is constantly accusing conservatives of being bigoted, intolerant, racist, and hateful. Typically, Democrats do this when they want to win an argument, win elections, or simply get what they want.
However, the irony in this is that Democrats repeatedly demonstrate bigotry, intolerance, and other similar traits. Just days ago, Joe Biden was telling Americans in Ohio about how much he misses having dinners with segregationist senators.
Biden also said during the 2020 presidential election that black Americans who voted for Trump, instead of himself, “ain’t black.”
Now, in another case of hatred and intolerance, New York is in the news for its own anti-Semitism, according to American Thinker.
Within the past several years, there’s been a growth of an anti-Semitic wing in the Democrat Party. Sadly, NYU Law is a part of this wing. In its Students For Justice in Palestine chapter, NYU Law took the liberty of supporting the violent murders of 3 Israeli men. Students For Justice in Palestine decided that covering these murderers made the media “Zionist.” The NYU Law chapter even justified the murders of these individuals.
Ironically, this is the same type of rhetoric to come from known anti-Semites, like former KKK Grand Wizard David Duke. Duke spread countless anti-Semitic tropes and conspiracies, just as this particular chapter from NYU Law has done.
Naturally, Jewish students took offense to this. In response to comments from Students For Justice in Palestine, Jewish students accused this chapter of breaking policies prohibiting discrimination and harassment.
Of course, Democrats in New York (and across America) are silent about this. New York Gov. Kathy Hochul (D) hasn’t said a word; the same also goes for NYC Mayor Eric Adams (D).
If Democrats truly cared about racism and intolerance, they’d be condemning the remarks from Students For Justice in Palestine. Instead, the political left continues to look the other way.
This, if nothing else, shows the true colors of the Democrat Party. They aren’t truly opposed to bigotry or hatred; they just use these things to score political points and further their own agendas.
It’s easier to accuse someone of being racist or bigoted than it is to debate them in good faith on policy issues. Thus far, Students For Justice in Palestine has not walked back its statement or apologized to the Jewish students who were offended. At this point, it’s only a matter of time before more similar incidents emerge from the political left.
